Note: SpringApplication is a predefined class and it will identify what type of application we have created based on dependencies added in pom.xml file.

1.if we add (Spring-boot-starter )-----------Standalone
=> For standalone application, it will use "AnnotationConfigApplicationContext" class will be used to start IoC container.

2. if we add-->(Spring-boot-web-starter) ----- web app
=> For web application, it will use   "AnnotationConfigServletWebAppApplicationContext" class will be used to start IoC container.

3.if we add-->(spring-boot-webflux-starter)   ------  reactive application
  => For reactive application, It will use "AnnotationConfigReactiveWebServerApplication" class will be used to start IoC container.

Note: Based on type of our application , It will start IOC container.

=> run() method will print banner on the console.(i.e  spring logo).
=> run() method will start IoC container.
=> run() method will call runners.
=> run () method will return context of IoC container.


============================================================
WHAT IS BANNER IN SPRING BOOT
============================================================

=> when we run boot application, it will print spring logo on the console that is called banner in spring boot.
=> Spring boot having 3 modes for banner set.
                
                1.off
                2.log
                3.console(default)
=> we can set banner mode using below property in "application.properties" file
             spring.main.banner-mode=off

=> We can customize banner text in spring boot application by using "banner.txt" file under src/main/resources folder.

